# Security Audit Master Skill
**Version:** 2.0.0  
**Type:** Self-Improving | Vulnerability Detection | Penetration Testing

## Core Purpose
Perform comprehensive security audits of applications to detect vulnerabilities, security flaws, potential intrusion points, API leaks, authentication bypasses, and overlooked security issues that could lead to data breaches or system compromise.

## Self-Improvement Engine
```yaml
learning_capabilities:
  - Track new vulnerability patterns (CVEs)
  - Learn from discovered exploits
  - Adapt to emerging attack vectors
  - Remember application-specific risks
  - Evolve detection algorithms
  - Update threat intelligence
```

## Security Audit Coverage

### 1. OWASP Top 10 (2023)
- **A01: Broken Access Control**
- **A02: Cryptographic Failures**
- **A03: Injection**
- **A04: Insecure Design**
- **A05: Security Misconfiguration**
- **A06: Vulnerable Components**
- **A07: Authentication Failures**
- **A08: Software & Data Integrity**
- **A09: Logging & Monitoring Failures**
- **A10: Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF)**

### 2. Additional Attack Vectors
- API Security (OWASP API Top 10)
- Business Logic Flaws
- Race Conditions
- Time-based Attacks
- Side-channel Attacks
- Supply Chain Attacks
- Zero-day Vulnerabilities

## Comprehensive Security Checklist

### **Authentication & Authorization Vulnerabilities**

```typescript
// ❌ CRITICAL FLAWS TO DETECT

// 1. Weak Password Storage
// BAD: Plain text or weak hashing
const badPasswordStorage = {
  password: userInput, // Plain text - CRITICAL
  password: md5(userInput), // MD5 is broken - CRITICAL
  password: sha1(userInput), // SHA1 is weak - HIGH
};

// GOOD: Strong hashing with salt
import bcrypt from 'bcrypt';
const saltRounds = 12;
const hashedPassword = await bcrypt.hash(password, saltRounds);

// 2. JWT Token Vulnerabilities
// BAD: Weak secret
const badJWT = jwt.sign(payload, 'secret'); // CRITICAL
const badJWT2 = jwt.sign(payload, process.env.JWT_SECRET, { algorithm: 'none' }); // CRITICAL

// BAD: No expiration
const noExpiry = jwt.sign(payload, secret); // HIGH

// GOOD: Strong secret with expiration
const goodJWT = jwt.sign(
  payload,
  process.env.JWT_SECRET, // 256+ bit random string
  {
    algorithm: 'HS256',
    expiresIn: '15m',
    issuer: 'your-app',
    audience: 'your-app-users',
  }
);

// 3. Session Fixation
// BAD: Reusing session ID after login
app.post('/login', (req, res) => {
  if (validCredentials) {
    req.session.user = user; // CRITICAL: Should regenerate session
  }
});

// GOOD: Regenerate session on login
app.post('/login', (req, res) => {
  if (validCredentials) {
    req.session.regenerate((err) => {
      req.session.user = user;
    });
  }
});

// 4. Insecure Direct Object Reference (IDOR)
// BAD: No authorization check
app.get('/api/users/:id', async (req, res) => {
  const user = await db.users.findById(req.params.id); // CRITICAL
  res.json(user);
});

// GOOD: Check ownership
app.get('/api/users/:id', auth, async (req, res) => {
  const requestedId = req.params.id;
  const currentUserId = req.user.id;
  
  if (requestedId !== currentUserId && !req.user.isAdmin) {
    return res.status(403).json({ error: 'Forbidden' });
  }
  
  const user = await db.users.findById(requestedId);
  res.json(user);
});

// 5. Missing Rate Limiting
// BAD: No rate limiting on sensitive endpoints
app.post('/api/login', loginHandler); // CRITICAL
app.post('/api/forgot-password', forgotHandler); // CRITICAL
app.post('/api/signup', signupHandler); // HIGH

// GOOD: Rate limiting implemented
import rateLimit from 'express-rate-limit';

const loginLimiter = rateLimit({
  windowMs: 15 * 60 * 1000, // 15 minutes
  max: 5, // 5 attempts
  standardHeaders: true,
  legacyHeaders: false,
  message: 'Too many login attempts, please try again later',
});

app.post('/api/login', loginLimiter, loginHandler);

// 6. Insufficient Authorization Checks
// BAD: Only checking authentication
app.delete('/api/posts/:id', isAuthenticated, async (req, res) => {
  await db.posts.delete(req.params.id); // CRITICAL: No ownership check
});

// GOOD: Check both authentication and authorization
app.delete('/api/posts/:id', isAuthenticated, async (req, res) => {
  const post = await db.posts.findById(req.params.id);
  
  if (!post) {
    return res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not found' });
  }
  
  if (post.authorId !== req.user.id && !req.user.isAdmin) {
    return res.status(403).json({ error: 'Forbidden' });
  }
  
  await db.posts.delete(req.params.id);
  res.json({ success: true });
});
```

### **Injection Vulnerabilities**

```typescript
// ❌ CRITICAL INJECTION FLAWS

// 1. SQL Injection
// BAD: Direct string concatenation
const badQuery = `SELECT * FROM users WHERE email = '${email}'`; // CRITICAL
const badQuery2 = db.query(`DELETE FROM posts WHERE id = ${req.params.id}`); // CRITICAL

// GOOD: Parameterized queries
const goodQuery = db.query('SELECT * FROM users WHERE email = ?', [email]);
const goodQuery2 = db.query('DELETE FROM posts WHERE id = $1', [req.params.id]);

// 2. NoSQL Injection
// BAD: Direct object usage
const user = await db.users.findOne({ 
  email: req.body.email, // CRITICAL if req.body.email = { $ne: null }
  password: req.body.password 
});

// GOOD: Type validation
const email = String(req.body.email);
const password = String(req.body.password);
const user = await db.users.findOne({ email, password: hashedPassword });

// 3. Command Injection
// BAD: Direct user input in exec
const { exec } = require('child_process');
exec(`convert ${req.body.filename} output.png`); // CRITICAL

// GOOD: Input validation and sanitization
const { execFile } = require('child_process');
const filename = path.basename(req.body.filename); // Remove path traversal
const allowedExtensions = ['.jpg', '.png', '.gif'];
const ext = path.extname(filename);

if (!allowedExtensions.includes(ext)) {
  throw new Error('Invalid file type');
}

execFile('convert', [filename, 'output.png']);

// 4. XSS (Cross-Site Scripting)
// BAD: Direct HTML rendering
app.get('/search', (req, res) => {
  const query = req.query.q;
  res.send(`<h1>Results for: ${query}</h1>`); // CRITICAL
});

// GOOD: Proper escaping
import escapeHtml from 'escape-html';
app.get('/search', (req, res) => {
  const query = escapeHtml(req.query.q);
  res.send(`<h1>Results for: ${query}</h1>`);
});

// React: Using dangerouslySetInnerHTML
// BAD
<div dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: userContent }} /> // CRITICAL

// GOOD: Use DOMPurify
import DOMPurify from 'dompurify';
<div dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ 
  __html: DOMPurify.sanitize(userContent) 
}} />

// 5. LDAP Injection
// BAD
const filter = `(uid=${username})`; // CRITICAL

// GOOD
import ldap from 'ldapjs';
const escapeLDAP = (str) => str.replace(/[*()\\]/g, '\\$&');
const filter = `(uid=${escapeLDAP(username)})`;

// 6. XML External Entity (XXE) Injection
// BAD: Default XML parser settings
const parser = new DOMParser();
const doc = parser.parseFromString(xmlData, 'text/xml'); // CRITICAL

// GOOD: Disable external entities
const libxmljs = require('libxmljs');
const doc = libxmljs.parseXml(xmlData, {
  noent: false, // Disable entity substitution
  dtdload: false, // Disable DTD loading
  doctype: false, // Disable doctype
});
```

### **API Security Vulnerabilities**

```typescript
// ❌ API SECURITY FLAWS

// 1. API Keys in Client-Side Code
// BAD: Exposed in frontend
const API_KEY = 'sk_live_51H4k2J3K4L5M6N7O8P9Q0'; // CRITICAL
const STRIPE_SECRET = process.env.STRIPE_SECRET; // CRITICAL if bundled to frontend

// GOOD: Server-side only
// Backend only - never send to client
const API_KEY = process.env.API_KEY; // Must stay on server

// 2. Missing API Authentication
// BAD: Public endpoint with sensitive data
app.get('/api/users', async (req, res) => {
  const users = await db.users.find(); // CRITICAL
  res.json(users);
});

// GOOD: Require authentication
app.get('/api/users', authenticateToken, authorizeAdmin, async (req, res) => {
  const users = await db.users.find({}, { password: 0, secretKey: 0 });
  res.json(users);
});

// 3. Excessive Data Exposure
// BAD: Returning full objects
app.get('/api/profile', auth, async (req, res) => {
  const user = await db.users.findById(req.user.id); // Includes password hash, secrets
  res.json(user); // CRITICAL
});

// GOOD: Selective field exposure
app.get('/api/profile', auth, async (req, res) => {
  const user = await db.users.findById(req.user.id, {
    select: 'id email name avatar createdAt',
  });
  res.json(user);
});

// 4. Mass Assignment
// BAD: Direct object update
app.patch('/api/users/:id', auth, async (req, res) => {
  await db.users.update(req.params.id, req.body); // CRITICAL: Can set isAdmin=true
});

// GOOD: Whitelist allowed fields
const allowedFields = ['name', 'bio', 'avatar'];
app.patch('/api/users/:id', auth, async (req, res) => {
  const updates = {};
  allowedFields.forEach(field => {
    if (req.body[field] !== undefined) {
      updates[field] = req.body[field];
    }
  });
  await db.users.update(req.params.id, updates);
});

// 5. CORS Misconfiguration
// BAD: Allow all origins
app.use(cors({ origin: '*' })); // CRITICAL

// BAD: Reflect origin
app.use(cors({ 
  origin: (origin, callback) => callback(null, origin) // CRITICAL
}));

// GOOD: Whitelist specific origins
const allowedOrigins = [
  'https://yourdomain.com',
  'https://app.yourdomain.com',
];

app.use(cors({
  origin: (origin, callback) => {
    if (!origin || allowedOrigins.includes(origin)) {
      callback(null, true);
    } else {
      callback(new Error('Not allowed by CORS'));
    }
  },
  credentials: true,
}));

// 6. Improper Error Handling
// BAD: Exposing stack traces
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  res.status(500).json({ 
    error: err.message,
    stack: err.stack, // CRITICAL: Exposes file paths, code structure
  });
});

// GOOD: Generic error messages
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  console.error(err); // Log for debugging
  
  const statusCode = err.statusCode || 500;
  const message = statusCode === 500 
    ? 'Internal server error' 
    : err.message;
  
  res.status(statusCode).json({ error: message });
});

// 7. GraphQL Introspection in Production
// BAD: Enabled in production
const server = new ApolloServer({
  schema,
  introspection: true, // CRITICAL in production
  playground: true, // CRITICAL in production
});

// GOOD: Disable in production
const server = new ApolloServer({
  schema,
  introspection: process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production',
  playground: process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production',
});
```

### **Cryptographic Failures**

```typescript
// ❌ CRYPTOGRAPHIC VULNERABILITIES

// 1. Weak Random Number Generation
// BAD: Math.random for security
const sessionId = Math.random().toString(36); // CRITICAL
const resetToken = Math.random().toString(36).substring(7); // CRITICAL

// GOOD: Cryptographically secure random
import crypto from 'crypto';
const sessionId = crypto.randomBytes(32).toString('hex');
const resetToken = crypto.randomBytes(32).toString('hex');

// 2. Hardcoded Secrets
// BAD: Secrets in code
const JWT_SECRET = 'my-secret-key'; // CRITICAL
const API_KEY = '12345abcde'; // CRITICAL
const ENCRYPTION_KEY = 'fixed-key'; // CRITICAL

// GOOD: Environment variables
const JWT_SECRET = process.env.JWT_SECRET;
const API_KEY = process.env.API_KEY;
const ENCRYPTION_KEY = process.env.ENCRYPTION_KEY;

// Validate on startup
if (!JWT_SECRET || JWT_SECRET.length < 32) {
  throw new Error('JWT_SECRET must be at least 32 characters');
}

// 3. Insecure Encryption
// BAD: ECB mode (deterministic)
const cipher = crypto.createCipher('aes-128-ecb', key); // CRITICAL

// GOOD: GCM mode (authenticated encryption)
const algorithm = 'aes-256-gcm';
const iv = crypto.randomBytes(16);
const cipher = crypto.createCipheriv(algorithm, key, iv);

// 4. Storing Sensitive Data Unencrypted
// BAD: Plain text in database
await db.creditCards.create({
  userId: user.id,
  cardNumber: req.body.cardNumber, // CRITICAL
  cvv: req.body.cvv, // CRITICAL
});

// GOOD: Encrypt or use payment gateway
// Never store CVV
// Use tokenization for card numbers
await stripe.customers.createSource(customerId, {
  source: cardToken, // Tokenized by Stripe
});

// 5. Insecure Communication
// BAD: HTTP for sensitive data
fetch('http://api.example.com/login', { // CRITICAL
  method: 'POST',
  body: JSON.stringify({ password }),
});

// GOOD: HTTPS only
fetch('https://api.example.com/login', {
  method: 'POST',
  body: JSON.stringify({ password }),
});

// Enforce HTTPS
app.use((req, res, next) => {
  if (!req.secure && process.env.NODE_ENV === 'production') {
    return res.redirect('https://' + req.headers.host + req.url);
  }
  next();
});
```

### **File Upload Vulnerabilities**

```typescript
// ❌ FILE UPLOAD SECURITY FLAWS

// 1. No File Type Validation
// BAD: Accept any file
app.post('/upload', upload.single('file'), (req, res) => {
  // CRITICAL: Can upload malicious files
  res.json({ path: req.file.path });
});

// GOOD: Strict validation
import path from 'path';
import mime from 'mime-types';

const allowedTypes = ['image/jpeg', 'image/png', 'image/gif'];
const allowedExtensions = ['.jpg', '.jpeg', '.png', '.gif'];

const fileFilter = (req, file, cb) => {
  const ext = path.extname(file.originalname).toLowerCase();
  const mimeType = file.mimetype;
  
  if (!allowedExtensions.includes(ext) || !allowedTypes.includes(mimeType)) {
    return cb(new Error('Invalid file type'));
  }
  
  cb(null, true);
};

const upload = multer({ 
  fileFilter,
  limits: { fileSize: 5 * 1024 * 1024 }, // 5MB
});

// 2. Path Traversal
// BAD: User-controlled filename
const filename = req.body.filename;
fs.writeFile(`./uploads/${filename}`, data); // CRITICAL: Can write to ../../etc/passwd

// GOOD: Sanitize filename
const filename = path.basename(req.body.filename); // Remove directory components
const safePath = path.join('./uploads', filename);

if (!safePath.startsWith(path.resolve('./uploads'))) {
  throw new Error('Invalid path');
}

// 3. File Execution
// BAD: Serving uploads from public directory
app.use('/uploads', express.static('uploads')); // CRITICAL: Can execute uploaded scripts

// GOOD: Serve with correct headers
app.get('/uploads/:filename', async (req, res) => {
  const filename = path.basename(req.params.filename);
  const filepath = path.join('./uploads', filename);
  
  res.setHeader('Content-Type', 'application/octet-stream');
  res.setHeader('X-Content-Type-Options', 'nosniff');
  res.sendFile(filepath);
});

// 4. ZIP Bomb / Decompression Bomb
// BAD: No size check before decompression
const unzip = require('unzip-stream');
fs.createReadStream(uploadPath).pipe(unzip.Extract({ path: './extracted' })); // CRITICAL

// GOOD: Check size before extraction
const maxSize = 100 * 1024 * 1024; // 100MB
let totalSize = 0;

fs.createReadStream(uploadPath)
  .pipe(unzip.Parse())
  .on('entry', (entry) => {
    totalSize += entry.size;
    
    if (totalSize > maxSize) {
      entry.autodrain();
      throw new Error('Archive too large');
    }
    
    entry.pipe(fs.createWriteStream(`./extracted/${entry.path}`));
  });
```

### **Business Logic Vulnerabilities**

```typescript
// ❌ BUSINESS LOGIC FLAWS

// 1. Race Conditions
// BAD: No transaction
app.post('/api/withdraw', auth, async (req, res) => {
  const user = await db.users.findById(req.user.id);
  
  if (user.balance >= req.body.amount) { // Race condition window
    user.balance -= req.body.amount;
    await user.save(); // CRITICAL: Can withdraw more than balance
  }
});

// GOOD: Use database transactions
app.post('/api/withdraw', auth, async (req, res) => {
  await db.transaction(async (trx) => {
    const user = await trx.users
      .findById(req.user.id)
      .forUpdate(); // Lock row
    
    if (user.balance < req.body.amount) {
      throw new Error('Insufficient balance');
    }
    
    await trx.users.update(req.user.id, {
      balance: user.balance - req.body.amount,
    });
  });
});

// 2. Integer Overflow
// BAD: No bounds checking
const quantity = parseInt(req.body.quantity);
const total = price * quantity; // CRITICAL: Can overflow

// GOOD: Validate bounds
const quantity = parseInt(req.body.quantity);

if (quantity < 0 || quantity > 1000000) {
  throw new Error('Invalid quantity');
}

const total = BigInt(price) * BigInt(quantity);

// 3. Time-of-check to Time-of-use (TOCTOU)
// BAD: Separate check and use
if (await hasPermission(user, resource)) { // Check
  await performAction(resource); // Use - permission might have changed
}

// GOOD: Atomic operation
await performActionWithPermissionCheck(user, resource);

// 4. Insufficient Anti-automation
// BAD: No CAPTCHA or challenge
app.post('/api/vote', async (req, res) => {
  await db.votes.create({ userId: req.user.id, postId: req.body.postId });
}); // CRITICAL: Can be automated

// GOOD: Add rate limiting + CAPTCHA
app.post('/api/vote', 
  rateLimiter,
  verifyCaptcha,
  async (req, res) => {
    // Check if already voted
    const existing = await db.votes.findOne({
      userId: req.user.id,
      postId: req.body.postId,
    });
    
    if (existing) {
      throw new Error('Already voted');
    }
    
    await db.votes.create({ userId: req.user.id, postId: req.body.postId });
  }
);

// 5. Price Manipulation
// BAD: Client sends price
app.post('/api/checkout', auth, async (req, res) => {
  const total = req.body.items.reduce((sum, item) => 
    sum + (item.price * item.quantity), 0 // CRITICAL: Client controls price
  );
});

// GOOD: Server calculates price
app.post('/api/checkout', auth, async (req, res) => {
  const items = await db.products.findMany({
    where: { id: { in: req.body.items.map(i => i.id) } },
  });
  
  const total = req.body.items.reduce((sum, item) => {
    const product = items.find(p => p.id === item.id);
    if (!product) throw new Error('Invalid product');
    
    return sum + (product.price * item.quantity);
  }, 0);
});
```

### **Infrastructure & Configuration**

```typescript
// ❌ INFRASTRUCTURE VULNERABILITIES

// 1. Exposed .env Files
// BAD: .env in git
// .gitignore missing .env
// CRITICAL: Secrets exposed in repository

// GOOD: Proper .gitignore
/*
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
*.key
*.pem
secrets/
*/

// 2. Debug Mode in Production
// BAD: Debug enabled
app.set('env', 'development'); // CRITICAL
const DEBUG = true; // CRITICAL

// GOOD: Environment-based
const DEBUG = process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production';

if (process.env.NODE_ENV === 'production') {
  app.set('env', 'production');
  app.disable('x-powered-by');
}

// 3. Default Credentials
// BAD: Default admin account
const admin = {
  username: 'admin',
  password: 'admin123', // CRITICAL
};

// GOOD: Force password change on first login
const admin = {
  username: process.env.ADMIN_USERNAME,
  password: await bcrypt.hash(process.env.ADMIN_PASSWORD, 12),
  mustChangePassword: true,
};

// 4. Exposed Admin Panels
// BAD: Public admin route
app.use('/admin', adminRoutes); // CRITICAL: No authentication

// GOOD: Protected admin routes
app.use('/admin', 
  requireAuth,
  requireRole('admin'),
  ipWhitelist,
  adminRoutes
);

// 5. Information Disclosure
// BAD: Verbose error messages
app.get('/api/user/:id', async (req, res) => {
  try {
    const user = await db.query('SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = ?', [req.params.id]);
    res.json(user);
  } catch (error) {
    res.status(500).json({ 
      error: error.message, // CRITICAL: May expose database structure
      query: error.sql, // CRITICAL
    });
  }
});

// GOOD: Generic errors in production
app.get('/api/user/:id', async (req, res) => {
  try {
    const user = await db.query('SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = ?', [req.params.id]);
    res.json(user);
  } catch (error) {
    logger.error(error); // Log internally
    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Internal server error' });
  }
});

// 6. Dependency Vulnerabilities
// BAD: Outdated dependencies
// package.json with old versions
// No security audits

// GOOD: Regular updates and audits
// npm audit
// npm update
// Use Dependabot or Snyk
// package.json with ^ or ~ for minor updates

// 7. Missing Security Headers
// BAD: No security headers
app.get('/', (req, res) => {
  res.send('Hello'); // Missing security headers
});

// GOOD: Helmet middleware
import helmet from 'helmet';

app.use(helmet({
  contentSecurityPolicy: {
    directives: {
      defaultSrc: ["'self'"],
      styleSrc: ["'self'", "'unsafe-inline'"],
      scriptSrc: ["'self'"],
      imgSrc: ["'self'", 'data:', 'https:'],
    },
  },
  hsts: {
    maxAge: 31536000,
    includeSubDomains: true,
    preload: true,
  },
  noSniff: true,
  xssFilter: true,
  referrerPolicy: { policy: 'same-origin' },
}));
```

## Automated Security Audit Script

```typescript
import fs from 'fs';
import path from 'path';
import { glob } from 'glob';

interface SecurityIssue {
  severity: 'CRITICAL' | 'HIGH' | 'MEDIUM' | 'LOW';
  category: string;
  description: string;
  file: string;
  line: number;
  code: string;
  recommendation: string;
}

class SecurityAuditor {
  private issues: SecurityIssue[] = [];
  
  // Dangerous patterns to detect
  private patterns = {
    // Authentication
    plainTextPassword: /password\s*[:=]\s*['"].*['"]/gi,
    weakHash: /(md5|sha1)\(/gi,
    noExpiry: /jwt\.sign\([^)]*\)(?![^)]*expiresIn)/gi,
    
    // Injection
    sqlInjection: /query\s*\(\s*['"`].*\$\{/gi,
    commandInjection: /exec\s*\(\s*['"`].*\$\{/gi,
    nosqlInjection: /findOne\s*\(\s*{\s*email\s*:\s*req\.body/gi,
    
    // XSS
    dangerousHTML: /dangerouslySetInnerHTML/gi,
    directHTML: /\.innerHTML\s*=/gi,
    
    // Secrets
    hardcodedSecret: /(api[_-]?key|secret|password|token)\s*[:=]\s*['"][^'"]{8,}['"]/gi,
    apiKeyExposed: /(sk_live|pk_live|key_|secret_|token_)[a-zA-Z0-9]{20,}/gi,
    
    // CORS
    corsAllOrigins: /cors\s*\(\s*{\s*origin\s*:\s*['"]?\*['"]?\s*}\s*\)/gi,
    
    // Crypto
    mathRandom: /Math\.random\(\)/gi,
    weakCipher: /createCipher\s*\(/gi,
    
    // File operations
    pathTraversal: /\$\{.*filename.*\}/gi,
    
    // HTTP
    httpNotHttps: /['"]http:\/\//gi,
  };
  
  async scanDirectory(directory: string): Promise<SecurityIssue[]> {
    const files = await glob('**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx}', {
      cwd: directory,
      ignore: ['node_modules/**', 'dist/**', 'build/**'],
    });
    
    for (const file of files) {
      await this.scanFile(path.join(directory, file));
    }
    
    return this.issues;
  }
  
  async scanFile(filepath: string): Promise<void> {
    const content = fs.readFileSync(filepath, 'utf-8');
    const lines = content.split('\n');
    
    lines.forEach((line, index) => {
      this.checkLine(line, index + 1, filepath);
    });
    
    // Check for missing security measures
    this.checkMissingSecurityMeasures(content, filepath);
  }
  
  private checkLine(line: string, lineNumber: number, file: string): void {
    // Plain text passwords
    if (this.patterns.plainTextPassword.test(line)) {
      this.addIssue({
        severity: 'CRITICAL',
        category: 'Authentication',
        description: 'Potential plain text password storage',
        file,
        line: lineNumber,
        code: line.trim(),
        recommendation: 'Use bcrypt or argon2 for password hashing',
      });
    }
    
    // Weak hashing
    if (this.patterns.weakHash.test(line) && line.includes('password')) {
      this.addIssue({
        severity: 'CRITICAL',
        category: 'Cryptography',
        description: 'Weak hashing algorithm for passwords (MD5/SHA1)',
        file,
        line: lineNumber,
        code: line.trim(),
        recommendation: 'Use bcrypt, scrypt, or argon2',
      });
    }
    
    // SQL Injection
    if (this.patterns.sqlInjection.test(line)) {
      this.addIssue({
        severity: 'CRITICAL',
        category: 'Injection',
        description: 'Potential SQL injection vulnerability',
        file,
        line: lineNumber,
        code: line.trim(),
        recommendation: 'Use parameterized queries or prepared statements',
      });
    }
    
    // Command Injection
    if (this.patterns.commandInjection.test(line)) {
      this.addIssue({
        severity: 'CRITICAL',
        category: 'Injection',
        description: 'Potential command injection vulnerability',
        file,
        line: lineNumber,
        code: line.trim(),
        recommendation: 'Use execFile with array of arguments, validate and sanitize input',
      });
    }
    
    // Hardcoded secrets
    if (this.patterns.hardcodedSecret.test(line)) {
      this.addIssue({
        severity: 'CRITICAL',
        category: 'Secrets Management',
        description: 'Hardcoded secret or API key detected',
        file,
        line: lineNumber,
        code: line.trim(),
        recommendation: 'Move to environment variables',
      });
    }
    
    // API key exposure
    if (this.patterns.apiKeyExposed.test(line)) {
      this.addIssue({
        severity: 'CRITICAL',
        category: 'Secrets Management',
        description: 'Exposed API key or secret token',
        file,
        line: lineNumber,
        code: line.trim(),
        recommendation: 'Remove from code, rotate key, use environment variables',
      });
    }
    
    // CORS misconfiguration
    if (this.patterns.corsAllOrigins.test(line)) {
      this.addIssue({
        severity: 'HIGH',
        category: 'CORS',
        description: 'CORS allows all origins (*)',
        file,
        line: lineNumber,
        code: line.trim(),
        recommendation: 'Whitelist specific origins',
      });
    }
    
    // Math.random for security
    if (this.patterns.mathRandom.test(line) && 
        (line.includes('token') || line.includes('session') || line.includes('id'))) {
      this.addIssue({
        severity: 'HIGH',
        category: 'Cryptography',
        description: 'Math.random() used for security-sensitive operation',
        file,
        line: lineNumber,
        code: line.trim(),
        recommendation: 'Use crypto.randomBytes() instead',
      });
    }
    
    // XSS vulnerabilities
    if (this.patterns.dangerousHTML.test(line)) {
      this.addIssue({
        severity: 'HIGH',
        category: 'XSS',
        description: 'dangerouslySetInnerHTML usage detected',
        file,
        line: lineNumber,
        code: line.trim(),
        recommendation: 'Sanitize content with DOMPurify before rendering',
      });
    }
    
    // HTTP in production
    if (this.patterns.httpNotHttps.test(line) && !line.includes('localhost')) {
      this.addIssue({
        severity: 'MEDIUM',
        category: 'Communication',
        description: 'HTTP URL detected (should use HTTPS)',
        file,
        line: lineNumber,
        code: line.trim(),
        recommendation: 'Use HTTPS for all external communications',
      });
    }
  }
  
  private checkMissingSecurityMeasures(content: string, file: string): void {
    // Check for helmet
    if (file.includes('server') || file.includes('app.ts')) {
      if (!content.includes('helmet')) {
        this.addIssue({
          severity: 'MEDIUM',
          category: 'Security Headers',
          description: 'Missing Helmet middleware for security headers',
          file,
          line: 0,
          code: '',
          recommendation: 'Add helmet() middleware',
        });
      }
      
      // Check for rate limiting
      if (!content.includes('rateLimit') && !content.includes('rate-limit')) {
        this.addIssue({
          severity: 'HIGH',
          category: 'Rate Limiting',
          description: 'No rate limiting detected',
          file,
          line: 0,
          code: '',
          recommendation: 'Implement rate limiting for all endpoints',
        });
      }
    }
    
    // Check .env in .gitignore
    if (file.endsWith('.gitignore')) {
      if (!content.includes('.env')) {
        this.addIssue({
          severity: 'CRITICAL',
          category: 'Secrets Management',
          description: '.env not in .gitignore',
          file,
          line: 0,
          code: '',
          recommendation: 'Add .env to .gitignore',
        });
      }
    }
  }
  
  private addIssue(issue: SecurityIssue): void {
    this.issues.push(issue);
  }
  
  generateReport(): string {
    const grouped = this.groupBySeverity();
    
    let report = '# Security Audit Report\n\n';
    report += `Total Issues Found: ${this.issues.length}\n\n`;
    
    ['CRITICAL', 'HIGH', 'MEDIUM', 'LOW'].forEach(severity => {
      const issues = grouped[severity] || [];
      if (issues.length === 0) return;
      
      report += `## ${severity} - ${issues.length} issues\n\n`;
      
      issues.forEach((issue, index) => {
        report += `### ${index + 1}. ${issue.category}: ${issue.description}\n`;
        report += `**File:** ${issue.file}:${issue.line}\n`;
        if (issue.code) {
          report += `**Code:** \`${issue.code}\`\n`;
        }
        report += `**Recommendation:** ${issue.recommendation}\n\n`;
      });
    });
    
    return report;
  }
  
  private groupBySeverity(): Record<string, SecurityIssue[]> {
    return this.issues.reduce((acc, issue) => {
      if (!acc[issue.severity]) acc[issue.severity] = [];
      acc[issue.severity].push(issue);
      return acc;
    }, {} as Record<string, SecurityIssue[]>);
  }
}

// Usage
const auditor = new SecurityAuditor();
const issues = await auditor.scanDirectory('./src');
console.log(auditor.generateReport());
```

## Dependency Security Scanner

```typescript
import { execSync } from 'child_process';
import fs from 'fs';

class DependencyScanner {
  async scanDependencies(): Promise<void> {
    console.log('Running npm audit...\n');
    
    try {
      const audit = execSync('npm audit --json', { encoding: 'utf-8' });
      const result = JSON.parse(audit);
      
      this.analyzeAuditResults(result);
    } catch (error: any) {
      if (error.stdout) {
        const result = JSON.parse(error.stdout);
        this.analyzeAuditResults(result);
      }
    }
    
    // Check for outdated packages
    console.log('\nChecking for outdated packages...\n');
    try {
      execSync('npm outdated', { encoding: 'utf-8', stdio: 'inherit' });
    } catch (error) {
      // npm outdated exits with 1 if packages are outdated
    }
  }
  
  private analyzeAuditResults(result: any): void {
    const { vulnerabilities } = result;
    
    if (!vulnerabilities) {
      console.log('No vulnerabilities found!');
      return;
    }
    
    const critical = Object.values(vulnerabilities).filter(
      (v: any) => v.severity === 'critical'
    ).length;
    
    const high = Object.values(vulnerabilities).filter(
      (v: any) => v.severity === 'high'
    ).length;
    
    console.log(`Critical: ${critical}`);
    console.log(`High: ${high}`);
    
    if (critical > 0 || high > 0) {
      console.log('\n⚠️  CRITICAL OR HIGH VULNERABILITIES FOUND!');
      console.log('Run: npm audit fix\n');
    }
  }
}
```

## Security Checklist for Code Review

```markdown
## Pre-Deployment Security Checklist

### Authentication & Authorization
- [ ] Passwords hashed with bcrypt/argon2 (min 10 rounds)
- [ ] JWT tokens have expiration
- [ ] JWT secret is strong (256+ bits) and in env variables
- [ ] Session regeneration on login
- [ ] Rate limiting on authentication endpoints
- [ ] Multi-factor authentication for sensitive operations
- [ ] Authorization checks on all protected endpoints
- [ ] No IDOR vulnerabilities

### Input Validation
- [ ] All user inputs validated and sanitized
- [ ] Parameterized queries for SQL
- [ ] Type checking for NoSQL queries
- [ ] File upload validation (type, size, content)
- [ ] Request size limits enforced
- [ ] Special characters escaped in outputs

### API Security
- [ ] No API keys in client-side code
- [ ] All sensitive endpoints require authentication
- [ ] CORS properly configured (no *)
- [ ] Rate limiting on all endpoints
- [ ] GraphQL introspection disabled in production
- [ ] Excessive data exposure prevented
- [ ] Mass assignment prevented

### Cryptography
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets
- [ ] Strong random number generation (crypto.randomBytes)
- [ ] HTTPS enforced
- [ ] Secure encryption algorithms (AES-256-GCM)
- [ ] Sensitive data encrypted at rest
- [ ] TLS 1.2+ only

### Error Handling
- [ ] No stack traces in production
- [ ] Generic error messages for users
- [ ] Detailed logs on server only
- [ ] No information disclosure

### Infrastructure
- [ ] .env in .gitignore
- [ ] Debug mode disabled in production
- [ ] Default credentials changed
- [ ] Security headers (Helmet)
- [ ] Dependencies up to date
- [ ] npm audit clean
- [ ] Admin panels protected

### File Operations
- [ ] Path traversal prevented
- [ ] File type validation
- [ ] File size limits
- [ ] Files served with correct headers
- [ ] Uploaded files not executed

### Business Logic
- [ ] Race conditions prevented (transactions)
- [ ] Price calculated server-side
- [ ] Anti-automation measures (CAPTCHA)
- [ ] Integer overflow checks
- [ ] Idempotency for critical operations

### Logging & Monitoring
- [ ] Security events logged
- [ ] Failed login attempts tracked
- [ ] Unusual activity alerts
- [ ] Audit trail for sensitive operations
```

